## 5. DATA SECURITY

### 5.1 How Your Data is Protected

**Local Data:**
- Protected by your device security (passcode, Face ID, Touch ID)
- Device encryption (if enabled) protects local data
- Most secure: we can't access what we don't have

**Data in Transit:**
- TLS/SSL encryption for all communications
- Encrypted connections to Apple and RevenueCat

### 5.2 Your Responsibilities

You can help protect your data by:
- Using a strong device passcode
- Enabling device encryption
- Not jailbreaking your device
- Installing iOS and app updates promptly
- Securing exported PDF files (contain sensitive data)

### 5.3 Exported PDFs

When you export session data to PDF:
- PDF is generated locally on your device
- We do NOT receive a copy
- The file is entirely your responsibility
- Consider password-protecting PDFs before sharing

